                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            <p>عين الحيوة</p>
                            <p>A Turkish mystical mathnawí, entitled 'Aynu'l-Hayát, or "The
                                Fountain of Life," by Ág-Kirmání Naqshí (according to the rubric on
                                f. 1 of W. 5), written partly in the hazaj metre and partly in
                                ramal, and beginning:</p>
                            <p>نه یوزده شرح ایدر بو کائناتی آیا کل اور بو كون عين الحياتي</p>
                            <p>The work, which is defective at the end, consists of a versified
                                exposition of Qur'anic texts and traditions of the Prophet.</p>
                            <p>Ff. 206 of 20 x 15 c. and 11 ll. Coarse Turkish hand, a mixture of
                                riq'a and díwání. Bought from J. J. Naaman in Sept., 1901.</p>
                        </summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="W_4-item1">
                            <author key="" cert="medium">
                                <persName xml:lang="ota-Latn-x">Ág-Kirmání Naqshí</persName>
                            </author>
                            <title xml:lang="ota-Latn-x" key="">'Aynu'l-Hayát</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ar">عين الحيوة</title>
                            <title xml:lang="en" type="desc">The Fountain of Life</title>
                            <note>A versified exposition of Qur'anic texts and traditions of the
                                Prophet, written partly in the hazaj metre and partly in ramal;
                                defective at the end. Cf. the complete copy at <ref
                                    target="../auto_update/W_5.xml">W. 5</ref>, whose rubric on f.
                                1 supplies the author's name.</note>
                            <incipit xml:lang="ota">نه یوزده شرح ایدر بو کائناتی آیا کل اور بو
                                كون عين الحياتي</incipit>
                            <explicit/>
                            <textLang mainLang="ota">Ottoman Turkish</textLang>
                        </msItem>
                    </msContents>
